00:56.290 --> 01:01.411
This is the story of a... a little boy.

01:03.297 --> 01:06.249
I'd say, "Stop me if you've heard this one

01:06.300 --> 01:10.970
before," but you have, and I
don't really want to be stopped.

01:11.621 --> 01:13.321
_

01:13.390 --> 01:17.310
This boy, he's a good
kid; not perfect, but good,

01:17.344 --> 01:20.313
and when he's about 10 years old,

01:20.347 --> 01:23.349
his mom and dad tell him
he's gonna have a baby sister.

01:23.400 --> 01:26.152
And the baby sister comes,

01:26.186 --> 01:29.822
and of course he loves her very much.

01:29.857 --> 01:34.110
But... she's getting attention.

01:34.161 --> 01:36.629
His attention.

01:36.664 --> 01:39.115
So he wishes...

01:39.117 --> 01:42.118
actually... he prays

01:42.169 --> 01:45.622
for that attention back and...

01:45.673 --> 01:48.641
a month later, he's diagnosed

01:48.676 --> 01:51.711
with acute lymphatic leukemia.

01:54.214 --> 01:57.467
And the... cancer eats away at the boy

01:57.518 --> 02:00.703
until there is almost nothing left.

02:00.738 --> 02:03.189
But he fights it.

02:03.223 --> 02:06.693
He survives and...

02:06.727 --> 02:09.696
now he has a choice to make.

02:09.729 --> 02:11.648
Does he decide

02:11.699 --> 02:13.816
that he was punished

02:13.867 --> 02:16.319
or that he was rewarded?

02:16.370 --> 02:19.389
Will he be angry for
having been made to suffer,

02:19.423 --> 02:21.357
or will he be grateful

02:21.392 --> 02:23.876
for that suffering because...

02:23.911 --> 02:26.162
it changed him?

02:30.050 --> 02:33.670
This is the story of a little girl.

02:35.089 --> 02:37.557
She's 8 years old, and

02:37.591 --> 02:42.345
just over a week ago,
she's playing in the park.

02:42.347 --> 02:45.348
She loves to go high on the swings,

02:45.350 --> 02:49.852
up to the point where you hang
there for a moment, suspended,

02:49.854 --> 02:55.024
before the chains clink and
gravity pulls you back down.

02:57.578 --> 03:01.080
She's been asleep...

03:01.115 --> 03:03.116
in a coma,

03:03.167 --> 03:05.034
for 9 days now.

03:05.085 --> 03:08.087
Her brain activity is negligible.

03:08.122 --> 03:12.208
Her outcome is undetermined.

03:13.961 --> 03:17.547
The girl's name is Emily...

03:20.768 --> 03:25.388
and so that little boy is
asking for attention again now.

03:27.808 --> 03:30.276
For Emily,

03:30.310 --> 03:32.895
let us pray.

03:37.334 --> 03:39.769
Heavenly Father,

03:39.803 --> 03:43.406
You invite all who are
burdened to come to You.

03:44.608 --> 03:48.211
Allow Your healing hand to touch this girl.

03:49.580 --> 03:52.465
Fill her heart with Your courage

03:52.499 --> 03:55.551
and infinite love for
all that you create...

04:08.849 --> 04:10.600
Please.

04:12.236 --> 04:15.154
- Oh! Oh!
- Stop please!

04:18.992 --> 04:20.610
Oh...

04:24.659 --> 04:25.888
_

06:25.569 --> 06:27.537
Well, it's probably not a concussion.

06:27.571 --> 06:29.739
Doctor will want to take a
look at you before you can go.

06:29.741 --> 06:31.908
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

06:33.377 --> 06:35.578
"Mrs. Amber Johnson,

06:35.629 --> 06:37.580
"a local pharmacist trainee,

06:37.631 --> 06:40.099
"secretly stole significant quantities

06:40.133 --> 06:42.919
"of Percocet, Oxycodone, and Vicodin

06:42.970 --> 06:45.421
and sold it to community college students."

06:45.472 --> 06:47.423
I know what it says.

06:47.474 --> 06:50.810
Amber here, she poof ed?

06:50.844 --> 06:53.312
She was a Departure, yes, mm-hmm.

06:53.347 --> 06:55.815
So you think our assailant knew Amber,

06:55.849 --> 06:58.234
maybe didn't appreciate
your little newsletter?

07:00.270 --> 07:01.771
I got this one, Lou.

07:01.822 --> 07:04.190
Chief, I was just taking his
statement. There's no need for...

07:04.224 --> 07:05.775
All right. Press charges, Matt?

07:05.777 --> 07:06.993
No.

07:07.027 --> 07:08.778
There you go.

07:10.163 --> 07:11.781
Father.

07:14.685 --> 07:16.619
Here we are again.

07:16.670 --> 07:18.287
Ahem.

07:19.623 --> 07:22.291
Occupational hazard. What are you gonna do?

07:22.342 --> 07:23.793
Stop pissin' people off.

07:23.844 --> 07:26.512
They need to hear the truth.

07:26.546 --> 07:28.631
Your dad understood that.

07:28.682 --> 07:31.300
Look where that got him.

07:34.104 --> 07:38.107
You know, me and Jill are living
in the old man's place now.

07:38.141 --> 07:41.110
Come over tonight, I'll
grill up some steaks,

07:41.144 --> 07:44.313
do a Sunday dinner like old times.

07:44.315 --> 07:47.900
Nights are tough for me.

07:47.951 --> 07:49.402
Mmm.

07:49.453 --> 07:50.870
Sorry.

07:59.162 --> 08:02.331
See you next time, Chief.

08:26.106 --> 08:29.191
Guess you and me are
going to the same place.

08:45.375 --> 08:47.376
You need help?

08:47.378 --> 08:49.345
Emily.

08:50.681 --> 08:54.300
The girl who was in here...
do you know what happened?

08:54.351 --> 08:56.552
She woke up,

08:56.603 --> 08:58.971
asked for a Sprite.

09:00.107 --> 09:02.058
Well, she's OK?

09:02.109 --> 09:04.560
I guess so. You know her?

09:04.562 --> 09:06.896
No, I visited with her, but

09:06.898 --> 09:09.398
my congregation...

09:09.449 --> 09:13.235
this morning, we prayed for her.

09:13.237 --> 09:16.288
Well, she woke up last night.

09:40.147 --> 09:43.232
Hello. You've reached the
administrative offices of Our Savior.

09:43.266 --> 09:45.434
Please leave a message
at the sound of the tone.

09:46.938 --> 09:49.371
Matt, hi. It's Jim Lewis from FDR.

09:49.406 --> 09:51.440
You're a hard man to reach.

09:51.442 --> 09:53.442
I'd really love to talk to you, in person,

09:53.444 --> 09:55.945
preferably, as soon as possible.

09:55.979 --> 09:58.948
I'm here at the bank
all day. Talk soon. Bye.

10:20.520 --> 10:22.471
Hey, hi.

10:22.473 --> 10:25.558
Um, are you open?

10:25.609 --> 10:27.760
Sure. Yeah. Come in.

10:29.146 --> 10:31.614
I don't know if you remember me.

10:31.648 --> 10:34.150
- I used to come all the time.
- Craig, right?

10:34.201 --> 10:35.734
McNary.

10:35.786 --> 10:38.654
Yeah. Sorry I haven't been in a while.

10:38.656 --> 10:41.157
My wife, ever since the 14th, she's not

10:41.159 --> 10:43.459
really into, you know...

10:45.212 --> 10:47.129
Anyway, she's over getting a manicure,

10:47.164 --> 10:49.131
and I told her to get her feet done, too,

10:49.166 --> 10:51.083
you know, just to take
some time for herself.

10:51.134 --> 10:54.170
I'd take the baby and come
back, pick her up later,

10:54.172 --> 10:56.172
so...

10:58.675 --> 11:01.177
How long does it take to do a,

11:01.179 --> 11:03.179
you know, a baptism?

11:47.724 --> 11:51.794
We... we have that
confidentiality thing, right?

11:51.828 --> 11:54.813
I'll try to keep my mouth shut.

11:56.449 --> 11:59.485
Oh, I... I don't know what the
appropriate contribution is...

11:59.536 --> 12:00.986
Please.

12:01.037 --> 12:02.988
It's on the house.

12:03.039 --> 12:05.124
You sure?

12:06.993 --> 12:08.911
How about you ask your wife to join

12:08.962 --> 12:11.497
you and your son for services this Sunday?

12:11.548 --> 12:14.466
We'll call it even.

12:14.501 --> 12:16.502
I don't think that's gonna happen.

12:16.553 --> 12:19.138
Heh! Had to try.

12:21.007 --> 12:24.143
If I don't, who will?

12:28.148 --> 12:30.599
This guy I worked with...

12:30.634 --> 12:32.601
he used to get loaded and drive out

12:32.603 --> 12:35.604
to the Indian casino in Connecticut.

12:35.606 --> 12:38.107
Gambled away his paycheck
every other Thursday.

12:38.109 --> 12:41.110
And when that was gone, I heard he...

12:41.112 --> 12:44.196
I heard he cleaned out
his kids' college account.

12:47.367 --> 12:49.535
He went on the 14th.

12:54.457 --> 12:57.042
What was his name?

12:59.846 --> 13:01.797
Andrew Sasaki.

13:04.302 --> 13:07.519
We don't discuss personal
information about our clientele.

13:07.554 --> 13:09.471
Sure. Of course not.

13:09.473 --> 13:12.975
This man, Mr. Sasaki, he was a Departure,

13:12.977 --> 13:16.278
and the reason I'm asking
about him is, uh... I'm sorry,

13:16.313 --> 13:20.482
I know this is personal, but did
you lose anyone close to you, sir?

13:24.237 --> 13:25.821
My niece.

13:27.290 --> 13:28.824
She was 9.

13:30.327 --> 13:32.328
May I show you something?

13:37.884 --> 13:40.002
This...

13:42.389 --> 13:44.974
is Albert Wayne Studdard.

13:45.008 --> 13:48.677
He abducted a young girl
walking home from school.

13:48.728 --> 13:51.847
Violated her sexually,
strangled her to death.

13:51.849 --> 13:55.351
On October 14th, he disappeared,

13:55.353 --> 13:57.853
right out of his jail cell.

13:57.855 --> 14:00.823
And this man, this monster,

14:00.857 --> 14:03.325
is on the same list
along with all the others

14:03.360 --> 14:06.862
who left us, along with
the innocent and the good...

14:06.913 --> 14:09.498
along with your niece.

14:10.867 --> 14:13.335
But someone has to expose these people

14:13.370 --> 14:16.338
for who they truly were
and what they truly did

14:16.373 --> 14:18.841
because if we can no longer separate

14:18.875 --> 14:21.293
the innocent from the guilty,

14:21.344 --> 14:24.880
everything that happened
to us, all of our suffering,

14:24.882 --> 14:26.849
is meaningless.

14:33.223 --> 14:36.225
I think I know what happened to your face.

14:36.227 --> 14:38.394
Can you help me?

14:39.813 --> 14:43.032
Well, we don't keep the
security cam data past 6 months,

14:43.066 --> 14:45.951
but I'll see what I can do.

14:45.985 --> 14:48.487
Jesus fucking Christ!

14:48.538 --> 14:49.905
Come on!

14:49.907 --> 14:52.958
What about the bet? What about the bet?

14:54.994 --> 14:57.396
Get outta here! Get outta here!

14:57.430 --> 15:00.632
I have to deal with
this. Get down to Pit 4.

15:00.667 --> 15:03.285
There's fuckin' birds on the table.

15:26.197 --> 15:28.197
_

15:38.338 --> 15:40.456
Oh.

16:04.114 --> 16:07.416
I'm sorry. I don't have any in white.

16:10.236 --> 16:13.238
I know you have a job to
do, but please tell Patti

16:13.289 --> 16:15.824
she's wasting your time sending you here.

16:15.826 --> 16:18.327
I've made it this far.

16:18.329 --> 16:21.997
I'm not gonna turn around now.

16:31.591 --> 16:33.058
Oh, Lord.

16:37.564 --> 16:39.648
What?

16:39.682 --> 16:42.151
Hello, Matt?

16:42.185 --> 16:45.604
Hey! Jim, is that you?

16:45.655 --> 16:48.357
I'm sorry. My phone's been acting up.

16:48.359 --> 16:51.360
Uh... how are you?

16:51.362 --> 16:53.712
Good. I'm good.

16:53.746 --> 16:57.282
Matt, I'm sure you're busy,
but can you come by the bank?

16:57.333 --> 16:58.367
Sure.

16:58.369 --> 17:00.369
- It's important.
- Yeah.

17:00.371 --> 17:02.788
I'll... come right over.

17:02.839 --> 17:04.790
Thank you!

17:09.762 --> 17:12.381
There's been an offer on the church.

17:13.766 --> 17:17.853
But... I don't understand.
You... you said I could stay.

17:17.887 --> 17:19.721
I said you could stay

17:19.771 --> 17:22.290
as long as no buyers came forward.

17:22.325 --> 17:24.726
I... I'm sorry, Matt.

17:24.728 --> 17:28.897
I've been trying to tell you
for at least two weeks now.

17:30.450 --> 17:33.035
Now, you always knew this could happen

17:33.069 --> 17:35.454
once you stopped making payments

17:35.488 --> 17:38.040
and we had to foreclose.

17:39.409 --> 17:41.243
Who's the buyer?

17:41.245 --> 17:43.045
Corporate LLC,

17:43.079 --> 17:45.797
probably a hedge fund.

17:45.832 --> 17:48.300
They can't really remodel,

17:48.334 --> 17:51.837
but the land is worth something.

17:53.306 --> 17:56.341
They probably want to knock it
down and throw up some apartments.

17:56.392 --> 17:58.594
Knock it...

17:58.645 --> 18:01.430
Well, it's not some restaurant.
This is a house of worsh...

18:06.486 --> 18:09.104
I'm sorry. I have to take this.

18:11.524 --> 18:12.941
Hey.

18:12.992 --> 18:14.493
Can I call you back?
I'm in the middle of a...

18:14.527 --> 18:16.495
We're out of bleach.

18:16.529 --> 18:18.614
What? Which kind?

18:18.665 --> 18:20.616
- Doesn't matter.
- Yeah.

18:20.667 --> 18:22.618
OK, I'll grab some on the way home.

18:22.669 --> 18:25.287
- Bye.
- Bye.

18:26.673 --> 18:28.790
How is Mary?

18:31.628 --> 18:34.296
Tell me how I can keep my church.

18:36.182 --> 18:38.133
With, uh, no other offers

18:38.135 --> 18:40.686
on the table, we have to accept theirs.

18:40.720 --> 18:43.639
But, now, if you can come in,

18:43.641 --> 18:46.608
all cash, even one dollar

18:46.643 --> 18:48.527
above their price,

18:48.561 --> 18:51.647
I can get your name back on the deed.

18:52.865 --> 18:54.983
What was their price?

18:57.704 --> 18:59.821
$135,000.

19:06.713 --> 19:09.331
How much time do I have?

19:11.217 --> 19:12.668
Tomorrow,

19:12.719 --> 19:14.303
end of day.

19:15.672 --> 19:17.673
Oh...

19:40.079 --> 19:41.580
- Hey, you.
- Hi.

19:41.614 --> 19:43.198
Hey.

19:48.037 --> 19:49.538
Bar fight?

19:51.041 --> 19:52.457
Am I interrupting anything?

19:52.508 --> 19:55.160
No, I was just watching TV. Come on in.

20:11.644 --> 20:13.995
Doug won't mind. I promise.

20:23.539 --> 20:25.490
Is Mary OK?

20:25.541 --> 20:28.126
She's... she's great.

20:30.046 --> 20:32.414
Then... what?

20:34.918 --> 20:38.587
I need to borrow $135,000.

20:39.972 --> 20:41.423
What?

20:41.474 --> 20:44.092
They're gonna sell the church.

20:51.484 --> 20:53.602
I'm sorry.

20:57.940 --> 20:59.941
I know it's a lot of money,

20:59.943 --> 21:01.910
but it'd just be a loan.

21:01.944 --> 21:04.413
Things are changing, people
are ready to come back.

21:04.447 --> 21:07.616
I just performed a baptism this morning.

21:08.951 --> 21:11.420
I hate coming to you,

21:11.454 --> 21:13.955
but this is our family church,

21:13.957 --> 21:15.674
Mom and Dad's...

21:15.708 --> 21:17.459
No, Matt, it's your church.

21:17.461 --> 21:18.627
They left it to both of us.

21:18.678 --> 21:20.629
They didn't leave it to anyone.

21:20.631 --> 21:23.298
They died in a fire when I
was 7, and then it was given...

21:23.349 --> 21:25.434
Please don't... don't get upset.

21:25.468 --> 21:27.969
- Why do you always have to do that?
- What?

21:27.971 --> 21:30.939
Make me upset and then
tell me not to get upset.

21:30.973 --> 21:33.191
You can't just knock on my
door and ask for $135,000...

21:33.226 --> 21:34.810
Do you not have it?

21:36.395 --> 21:39.030
I thought the benefit money...

21:42.034 --> 21:45.704
That money was for my
husband and my children.

21:49.325 --> 21:51.460
I'm sorry.

21:52.879 --> 21:54.796
You're right.

21:54.831 --> 21:58.300
I shouldn't have asked. I just...

21:58.334 --> 22:00.969
didn't know where to go.

22:09.679 --> 22:12.314
Will you stop making your paper?

22:13.432 --> 22:14.850
What?

22:14.901 --> 22:16.852
You're asking me for something.

22:16.936 --> 22:18.854
I'm asking you for something.

22:18.856 --> 22:21.823
Stop making your paper and
I'll give you the money.

22:21.858 --> 22:23.241
- I can't do that.
- Why not?

22:23.276 --> 22:24.493
People need to hear the tru...

22:24.527 --> 22:26.161
People need to punch you in the face!

22:26.195 --> 22:28.330
I didn't say it was easy to hear.

22:28.364 --> 22:30.115
Then deliver the truth in your church.

22:30.166 --> 22:31.833
That's what you're asking
me for, right, your church?

22:31.868 --> 22:33.535
- That's not what this is about.
- No!

22:33.537 --> 22:36.505
It's about the accident!
It's about the judge!

22:36.539 --> 22:39.508
And it should have ended
there, but you kept going!

22:39.542 --> 22:42.511
You dug up your dirt, and people
called you crazy behind your back,

22:42.545 --> 22:45.046
and I defended you because
I knew you were in pain,

22:45.048 --> 22:47.182
but then you decided it was your calling,

22:47.216 --> 22:49.885
your... your purpose, like you
were personally selected by God...

22:49.887 --> 22:52.637
Don't say that word! Don't say that word.

22:52.688 --> 22:56.057
You don't get to talk about
something you don't believe in.

22:56.059 --> 22:58.527
I don't get to?

22:58.561 --> 23:01.530
What do you believe in, Matt?

23:01.564 --> 23:05.066
Do you know where my family went?

23:05.068 --> 23:08.203
Do you know what it was?

23:13.242 --> 23:15.710
It was a test.

23:15.745 --> 23:17.746
Oh.

23:19.415 --> 23:21.583
Not for what came before,

23:21.585 --> 23:24.252
but for what came after.

23:24.303 --> 23:27.339
It was a test for what comes now.

23:27.390 --> 23:29.758
Well, if it was a test,

23:29.760 --> 23:32.928
then I think you may be failing it.

23:47.109 --> 23:49.744
I love you, Matt...

23:53.115 --> 23:55.617
but what you're doing...

23:55.619 --> 23:57.619
your paper, the church...

23:57.621 --> 24:00.121
it's not working anymore.

24:01.958 --> 24:05.126
It's not making things better.

24:07.597 --> 24:20.025
Maybe it's time to let it go.

24:20.059 --> 24:22.143
Hmm.

24:25.364 --> 24:27.782
Doug was having an affair.

24:34.156 --> 24:36.241
The kids' preschool teacher.

24:37.627 --> 24:40.745
They usually did it at her apartment.

24:42.665 --> 24:45.583
But a couple of times,

24:45.635 --> 24:49.254
he brought her to The Plaza in the city.

24:51.974 --> 24:55.894
He was smart enough to use cash, but...

24:55.928 --> 25:00.098
I have the receipts from
the ATM in their lobby.

25:05.971 --> 25:08.490
It's the one story I will never publish.

25:24.774 --> 25:27.542
I love you. I love you, too.

25:28.961 --> 25:30.595
OK.

25:46.696 --> 25:50.865
They're gone, but so much
of them is still here.

25:53.185 --> 25:56.738
You've tried to move on,
tried to live a normal life,

25:56.740 --> 25:59.207
but you haven't let go

25:59.241 --> 26:01.876
because you haven't known how.

26:03.379 --> 26:07.882
Loved Ones bereavement figures
allow you to say that good-bye.

